HEADWORD: Creator
<hw>Cre*a"tor</hw> <pr>(kr⟦esl⟧*⟦amac⟧"t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>creator</ets>: cf. F. <ets>cr⟦eacute⟧ateur</ets>.]</ety>
<def>One who creates, produces, or constitutes. Specifically, the
Supreme Being.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To sin's rebuke and my <qex>Creater's</qex> praise.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The poets and artists of Greece, who are at the same time its
prophets, the <qex>creators</qex> of its divinities, and the revealers
of its theological beliefs.</q> <rj><qau>Caird.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Creatorship</ent>⟦br⟧
